{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id90b18de3-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6215"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6215"},"text":"§ 6215.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Establishment of Radio Free Afghanistan","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id90b18de4-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6215/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Requirement of a detailed plan","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Not later than 15 days after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-03-11"},"text":"March 11, 2002","children":[],"tail":", RFE/RL, Incorporated, shall submit to the Broadcasting Board of Governors a report setting forth a detailed plan for the provision by RFE/RL, Incorporated, of surrogate broadcasting services in the Dari and Pashto languages to Afghanistan. Such broadcasting services shall be known as “Radio Free Afghanistan”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id90b18de5-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6215/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Grant authority","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id90b18de6-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6215/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Effective 15 days after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-03-11"},"text":"March 11, 2002","children":[],"tail":", or the date on which the report required by subsection (a) is submitted, whichever is later, the Broadcasting Board of Governors is authorized to make grants to support Radio Free Afghanistan."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id90b18de7-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6215/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Supersedes existing limitation on total annual grant amounts","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Grants made to RFE/RL, Incorporated, during the fiscal year 2002 for support of Radio Free Afghanistan may be made without regard to section 308(c) of the United States International Broadcasting Act of 1994 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s6207/c"},"text":"22 U.S.C. 6207(c)","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id90b18de8-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6215/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Available authorities","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In addition to the authorities in this section, the authorities applicable to carry out United States Government broadcasting activities under the United States Information and Educational Exchange Act of 1948 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s1431"},"text":"22 U.S.C. 1431","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], the United States International Broadcasting Act of 1994 ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s6201"},"text":"22 U.S.C. 6201","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], the Foreign Affairs Reform and Restructuring Act of 1998, and other provisions of law consistent with such purpose may be used to carry out the grant authority of subsection (b)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id90b18de9-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6215/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Standards; oversight","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Radio Free Afghanistan shall adhere to the same standards of professionalism and accountability, and shall be subject to the same oversight mechanisms, as other services of RFE/RL, Incorporated.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id90b18dea-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/148/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–148, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-03-11"},"text":"Mar. 11, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/64"},"text":"116 Stat. 64","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id90b18deb-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id90b18dec-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id90b18ded-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The United States Information and Educational Exchange Act of 1948, referred to in subsec. (c), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-01-27/ch36"},"text":"act Jan. 27, 1948, ch. 36","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/6"},"text":"62 Stat. 6","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to chapter 18 (§ 1431 et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s1431"},"text":"section 1431 of this title","children":[],"tail":", and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The United States International Broadcasting Act of 1994, referred to in subsec. (c), is title III of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/236"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–236","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-04-30"},"text":"Apr. 30, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/432"},"text":"108 Stat. 432","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to this chapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s6201"},"text":"section 6201 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Foreign Affairs Reform and Restructuring Act of 1998, referred to in subsec. (c), is division G of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1998","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/112/2681-761"},"text":"112 Stat. 2681–761","children":[],"tail":". For complete classification of division G to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s6501"},"text":"section 6501 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id90b18dee-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the Radio Free Afghanistan Act, and not as part of the United States International Broadcasting Act of 1994 which comprises this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id90b18def-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"id90b18df0-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Broadcasting Board of Governors renamed United States Agency for Global Media pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s6204/a/21"},"text":"section 6204(a)(21) of this title","children":[],"tail":". The renaming was effectuated by notice to congressional appropriations committees dated "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-05-24"},"text":"May 24, 2018","children":[],"tail":", and became effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-08-22"},"text":"Aug. 22, 2018","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
